OL,3,CTwo in five drivers say they have no
OL,4,Calternative to the car for commuting
OL,6,FTaking the bus to work was only seen
OL,7,Fas a viable option for 31% of drivers,
OL,8,Frising to 50% for residents of town
OL,9,Fand city centres where public
OL,10,Ftransport provision is generally
OL,11,Fhighest.
OL,13,FJust 26% of drivers living in suburbs
OL,14,Fsaid they could commute by bus.
OL,16,FMore than four out of five (81%)
OL,17,Frespondents said they would find it
OL,18,Fvery difficult to adjust their
OL,19,Flifestyle to being without a vehicle.
