OL,6,FThe proportion of drivers saying they
OL,7,Fwould struggle to adjust to life
OL,8,Fwithout a vehicle rose from 65% for
OL,9,Funder-25s, to 77% for those aged 25-
OL,10,F44, 84% for those aged 45-64, and 86%
OL,11,Ffor those aged 65 and over.
OL,13,FMore than half of drivers (53%) said
OL,14,Fthey would use their vehicle less if
OL,15,Fpublic transport was more convenient,
OL,16,Freliable and affordable.
OL,18,FRAC head of policy Simon Williams
OL,19,Fsaid: "Our research shows that the car
OL,20,Fremains central to so many people's
OL,21,Flives.
